{{Quote|I ended up winning an Academy Award for ''Star Wars'' before I'd even started thinking about winning Academy Awards.|Paul Hirsch, about the unexpected success of ''Star Wars''|<ref name="eod">''[[Empire of Dreams: The Story of the Star Wars Trilogy]]''</ref>}}
'''Paul Hirsch''' (Born [[November 14]], [[1940s|1945]]) is a motion picture editor. In [[1978]], he, along with [[Richard Chew]] and [[Marcia Lucas]], won the Academy Award for Film Editing for his work on [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'']].

He is credited for coining the phrase "It's sound people, or worse!" to chide the sound crew whenever they appeared, paraphrasing [[Luke Skywalker]]'s line about the [[Tusken Raider|Sand People]] in ''Star Wars''. Inspired from this, the sound crew designed and wore t-shirts with this phrase, depicting a Tusken holding a boom pole instead of a [[Gaderffii stick]].<ref>[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']]</ref>

